-- Hungarian Refiner Mol Has Third Week of Gains as Crude Advances
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-01-27T16:45:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/hungary-s-mol-heads-for-third-week-of-gains-as-crude-advances.html
Mol Nyrt. (MOL) , Hungary’s largest
refiner, extended a third week of advances as oil rose.  The shares advanced 3 percent to 19,565 forint at the close
in Budapest, extending this week’s gain to 1.9 percent. The
shares have rallied 20 percent since the close on Jan. 6.  Crude for March delivery on the  New York Mercantile
Exchange  climbed 0.8 percent to $100.49 a barrel today.  Hungary’s BUX index of shares gained 0.8 percent to
19,286.15, a 2.3 percent weekly increase.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  